  "text": "# Django Model Field Validation Coverage Audit\n\n## Overview\n\nThis audit identifies all Python source files in django/django that implement model field validators and the validation pipeline for both model and form fields.\n\n## Core Validators (django/core/validators.py)\n\nThe file `django/core/validators.py` contains all built-in Django validators:\n\n### Validator Classes:\n- **RegexValidator** (line 20): Base validator using regex patterns with support for inverse matching\n- **DomainNameValidator** (line 69): Validates domain names using regex patterns, supporting both IDNA and ASCII-only modes\n- **URLValidator** (line 130): Validates URLs including IPv4, IPv6, and domain names with configurable schemes\n- **EmailValidator** (line 210): Validates email addresses with domain allowlist support\n- **BaseValidator** (line 380): Abstract base class for limit-based validators (MaxValue, MinValue, MaxLength, MinLength)\n- **MaxValueValidator** (line 415): Ensures values do not exceed a maximum\n- **MinValueValidator** (line 424): Ensures values meet a minimum threshold\n- **StepValueValidator** (line 433): Ensures values are multiples of a step size\n- **MinLengthValidator** (line 471): Ensures minimum length for sequences/strings\n- **MaxLengthValidator** (line 489): Ensures maximum length for sequences/strings\n- **DecimalValidator** (line 507): Validates decimal field precision and scale\n- **FileExtensionValidator** (line 595): Validates file extensions against an allowlist\n- **ProhibitNullCharactersValidator** (line 656): Prevents null characters in strings\n\n### Validator Functions:\n- validate_integer: Validates integer strings\n- validate_ipv4_address: Validates IPv4 addresses\n- validate_ipv6_address: Validates IPv6 addresses\n- validate_ipv46_address: Validates both IPv4 and IPv6 addresses\n- validate_email: Instance of EmailValidator\n- validate_slug: Validates slug format using RegexValidator\n- validate_unicode_slug: Validates unicode slug format\n- validate_domain_name: Instance of DomainNameValidator\n- int_list_validator: Factory function for comma-separated integer validation\n- ip_address_validators: Factory function returning appropriate IP validators\n\n## PostgreSQL-Specific Validators (django/contrib/postgres/validators.py)\n\nThe file `django/contrib/postgres/validators.py` contains PostgreSQL array and range validators:\n\n- **ArrayMaxLengthValidator** (line 13): Extends MaxLengthValidator for array fields\n- **ArrayMinLengthValidator** (line 23): Extends MinLengthValidator for array fields\n- **KeysValidator** (line 34): Validates HStore key presence and restrictions\n- **RangeMaxValueValidator** (line 76): Validates upper bounds of range fields\n- **RangeMinValueValidator** (line 85): Validates lower bounds of range fields\n\n## Model Field Validation (django/db/models/fields/__init__.py)\n\nThe Field class implements the core validation pipeline:\n\n- **Field.clean(value, model_instance)** (line 829): Main entry point that:\n  1. Calls to_python() to convert values\n  2. Calls validate() for field-level validation\n  3. Calls run_validators() to execute all registered validators\n  4. Returns cleaned value\n\n- **Field.validate(value, model_instance)** (line 798): Base implementation checking:\n  - Editable field restriction\n  - Choice validation\n  - Null constraints\n  - Blank constraints\n\n- **Field.run_validators(value)** (line 782): Executes all validators from self.validators property, aggregating errors\n\nFields automatically populate default validators based on their type (e.g., CharField adds MaxLengthValidator when max_length is set).\n\n## Model-Level Validation (django/db/models/base.py)\n\nThe Model class implements the complete validation workflow:\n\n### Main Validation Pipeline:\n- **Model.full_clean(exclude=None, validate_unique=True, validate_constraints=True)** (line 1690): Orchestrates all validation steps:\n  1. Calls clean_fields() for individual field validation\n  2. Calls clean() for model-wide custom validation\n  3. Calls validate_unique() for uniqueness constraints\n  4. Calls validate_constraints() for database constraints\n\n### Field-Level Validation:\n- **Model.clean_fields(exclude=None)** (line 1737): Iterates through model fields calling Field.clean() for each field value (line 1758: `f.clean(raw_value, self)`)\n\n### Model-Level Validation Hook:\n- **Model.clean()** (line 1440): Empty hook for subclasses to implement custom validation logic\n\n### Uniqueness Validation:\n- **Model.validate_unique(exclude=None)** (line 1450): Validates unique constraints by calling:\n  - _get_unique_checks() (line 1466): Gathers all unique constraint checks from field definitions and Meta.unique_together\n  - _perform_unique_checks() (line 1534): Executes database queries to verify uniqueness\n  - _perform_date_checks() (line 1583): Checks unique_for_date, unique_for_month, unique_for_year constraints\n\n### Constraint Validation:\n- **Model.validate_constraints(exclude=None)** (line 1670): Validates database constraints by calling constraint.validate() on each constraint object\n- **Model.get_constraints()** (line 1663): Collects constraints from model and parent classes\n\n## Form Field Validation (django/forms/fields.py)\n\nForm fields implement a similar validation pattern to model fields:\n\n- **Field.clean(value)** (line 202): Main entry point that:\n  1. Calls to_python() for value conversion\n  2. Calls validate() for field-level validation\n  3. Calls run_validators() to execute validators\n  4. Returns cleaned value\n\n- **Field.validate(value)** (line 184): Base implementation checking only the required attribute\n\n- **Field.run_validators(value)** (line 188): Executes all validators, aggregating errors\n\n## Form Validation (django/forms/forms.py)\n\nThe BaseForm class implements the form validation pipeline:\n\n- **BaseForm.full_clean()** (line 324): Main entry point that:\n  1. Initializes error dictionary\n  2. Calls _clean_fields() to validate individual fields\n  3. Calls _clean_form() to validate overall form\n  4. Calls _post_clean() for subclass hooks (used by ModelForm)\n\n- **BaseForm._clean_fields()** (line 341): Iterates through fields calling Field.clean() via _clean_bound_field()\n\n- **BaseForm._clean_form()** (line 352): Calls clean() method for form-wide validation\n\n- **BaseForm.clean()** (line 368): Empty hook for custom form validation logic\n\n## ModelForm Validation (django/forms/models.py)\n\nModelForm extends form validation with model integration:\n\n- **ModelForm.full_clean()**: Extends BaseForm.full_clean() with model instance validation\n- **ModelForm.validate_unique()** (line 515): Calls model's validate_unique() method\n- **ModelForm.validate_constraints()** (line 526): Calls model's validate_constraints() method\n- **ModelForm._post_clean()** (line 453+): Calls model.full_clean() with appropriate exclude parameter\n\n## Validation Pipeline Summary\n\n### Model Instance Validation:\n```\nModel.full_clean()\n├── clean_fields()\n│   └── Field.clean(value, model_instance)\n│       ├── to_python()\n│       ├── validate()\n│       └── run_validators()\n├── clean() [hook for custom validation]\n├── validate_unique()\n│   ├── _get_unique_checks()\n│   ├── _perform_unique_checks()\n│   └── _perform_date_checks()\n└── validate_constraints()\n    └── Constraint.validate()\n```\n\n### Form Validation:\n```\nForm.full_clean()\n├── _clean_fields()\n│   └── Field.clean(value)\n│       ├── to_python()\n│       ├── validate()\n│       └── run_validators()\n├── _clean_form()\n│   └── clean() [hook for custom validation]\n└── _post_clean() [ModelForm integration]\n    └── instance.full_clean()\n```\n\n## Key Integration Points\n\n1. **Field Validators**: All field validators inherit from BaseValidator or RegexValidator pattern and implement __call__(value) method\n2. **Validator Discovery**: Fields use default_validators + _validators property to determine which validators to run\n3. **Error Aggregation**: All validators in run_validators() are executed and errors aggregated before raising ValidationError\n4. **Model Integration**: Model.clean_fields() calls field.clean() with both value and model instance for context-aware validation\n5. **Form Integration**: Forms validate fields independently, then optionally validate at form and model level\n6. **Constraint Validation**: Database constraints (CheckConstraint, UniqueConstraint) have their own validate() methods called during model validation"
